summary: Surpriiiiiiiiiiise xD Sorry I didn’t ask first but I couldn’t help myself!! Last night I was doodling Yoora (1st) and got the...
caption:
Surpriiiiiiiiiiise xD Sorry I didn’t ask first but I couldn’t help myself!! Last night I was doodling Yoora (1st) and got the idea of a poster of ocs for the clone wars! It would be a huge project so I’m first breaking it down by oc in a mini poster form, kind of like trading cards xD

Yoora belongs to @anyakinskywalker 

Telusa belongs to @bunniexheartx

Tee’kai belongs to @kocreation

If you would like me to draw your oc I would be happy to do so!! Just send me a message, a reference or two, and I’ll doodle them soon! (tbh I might have already started yours since I’ve been hunting down the Clone wars oc tag for bbys to draw) 

I hope you guys like them!! :)

May the Force be with you, always.

title: ATTENTION ARTISTS!
body:
I’m making a LinkedIn profile for my art, but I have no professional art education (I’m self-taught, through free online courses, imitation, and practice), and no freaking clue how to make myself not look like a Pinterest Mom Artist/ hobbyist wannabe.

I am a fairly animated and articulate person… in… person, but trying to describe my learning and experience in a way that makes me a fun, relatable and professional person online, I end up falling super flat and I am terrible at it.

Do you have any advice or resources that can help me figure out how to ‘sell myself’ online, as this is a large part of trying to make it anywhere?

Thank you so much in advance. <3

summary: References for Roni, including an age progression sheet: 5 y/o: Before she was separated from her brothers and still living in a...
caption:
References for Roni, including an age progression sheet:

5 y/o: Before she was separated from her brothers and still living in a secret institution being lightly experimented upon.

7 y/o: When she was living  happily with her adoptive mother and two sisters, her powers still kept secret

11 y/o: Everything goes to shit, her adoptive mother disappears, she’s alone with her sisters are put back into foster care under special conditions after their  powers their exposed, meanwhile fearing that the three of them might be separated. The news also brings to light the discovery of other kids like them in the same area.

13,14, and 15 y/o: Very experimental years, in more ways than one…

17 y/o: At peace with herself and her situation, doing her best to live her best life.
